whoot! PS I was going to mention a trick for experimenting with the
adjuster stuff.

you can auto-configure a wrapper like we do for tracing. in your storage
wrapper, you wrap the span consumer.. inject and test your filter/adjusters
this way (as a pre-step to storage which is correct anyway). Might help
decoupling


@Configuration
static class AdjustingStorageComponentEnhancer implements BeanPostProcessor {

  @Autowired(required = false)
  YourStuff yourStuff;

  @Override
  public Object postProcessBeforeInitialization(Object bean, String beanName) {
    return bean;
  }

  @Override
  public Object postProcessAfterInitialization(Object bean, String beanName) {
    if (yourStuff == null) return bean;
    if (bean instanceof StorageComponent) {
      return new AdjustingStorageComponent(yourStuff, (StorageComponent) bean);
    }
    return bean;
  }
}
